---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'; import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Visual language — Leicester Space Week brand"><PageHero eyebrow="Visual language" title="Signals of curiosity." intro="Supporting elements extend the identity without competing with the crest. Use them to create rhythm, location and a sense of connected exploration." /><section class="section motif"><div class="shell"><div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">Motif library</p><h2>Orbit. Stars.<br />A city skyline.</h2></div><div class="cards"><article class="card"><span class="glyph">◌</span><div><h3>Orbital lines</h3><p>Fine Steel Silver or Paper White arcs express movement and connection. Keep them quiet, cropped and secondary to content.</p></div></article><article class="card"><span class="glyph">✦</span><div><h3>Stars</h3><p>Use sparse points of light as a small moment of discovery. Never turn them into a decorative pattern.</p></div></article><article class="card"><span class="glyph">⌂</span><div><h3>Skyline</h3><p>Use a single-weight, continuous line to anchor large-format work in Leicester. It should sit low and never compete with the fox.</p></div></article></div></div></section><section class="section"><div class="shell"><div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">Photography</p><h2>Real work. Real wonder.</h2><p>Photography makes the identity tangible. Prioritise research, engineering, learning, making and the people who bring space down to earth.</p></div><div class="usage"><article class="usage-panel do"><span class="check">✓</span><h3>Show participation</h3><p>Use candid, thoughtful images of people collaborating, building, testing and sharing knowledge. Let Leicester locations appear naturally.</p></article><article class="usage-panel dont"><span class="cross">×</span><h3>Avoid visual shorthand</h3><p>Avoid generic astronaut stock, cartoon rockets, sci-fi interfaces and images that feel distant from the city’s real space community.</p></article></div></div></section></BaseLayout>
